OL,7,FA statement on the park's website
OL,8,Fsaid: "Despite significant and ongoing
OL,9,Finvestment since its rescue from
OL,10,Fclosure in 2012 by the current owners,
OL,11,Frising costs and a steady decline in
OL,12,Fvisitor numbers have made the park's
OL,13,Foperation and further investment
OL,14,Funsustainable.
OL,16,F"Over the years, Flambards has strived
OL,17,Fto evolve, overcoming numerous
OL,18,Fchallenges to continue bringing joy to
OL,19,Ffamilies and visitors from across the
OL,20,Fregion."
